    "Purpose": "Requirements for delivery and installation in the test environment",
    "Test steps": "The supplier shall upon delivery and installation of  the measurement system in the client's test environment: \n- install, \n- configure / parameterize, \n- if necessary, migrate structural data, \n- carry out tests of similar scope as the FAT, including system integration tests (SIT), and \n- carry out corrections and re-tests."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-28",
    "Purpose": "Structural data in HES",
    "Test steps": "Verify that it is possible to manually register structure data in HES."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-29",
    "Purpose": "Highest deviation not to exceed 7 seconds",
    "Test steps": "Verify the time of the measuring unit for at least 10 meters before synchronizatioin with HES is performed. Verify that time of the measurements units adter synchronization with HES is completed."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-30",
    "Purpose": "Reports based on status",
    "Test steps": "Verify that status is included for measurements in the reports we generate."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-31",
    "Purpose": "Importing of measurement data",
    "Test steps": "Verify that HES has functionality to import measurement data from a standardized text file format, such as csv."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-32",
    "Purpose": "Form views",
    "Test steps": "Verify that form views exist for presenting and entering/modifying structural data."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-33",
    "Purpose": "Filtering and sorting in the alarm list ",
    "Test steps": "Verify that a User can filter and sort the alarm list. "
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-34",
    "Purpose": "Copying static fields ",
    "Test steps": "Verify that it is possible to copy static fields in HES such as headers, status, responses to events in the system."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-35",
    "Purpose": "Inactivating the sending of Events from specific Measurement Units ",
    "Test steps": "Verify that it is possible to disable the transmission of events from a designated Measurement Unit to HES, in order to avoid receiving a large volume of events from a specific Measurement Unit"
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-36",
    "Purpose": "98.0 %  to HES 4h after day-shift",
    "Test steps": "Verify that there are routines that describe that we continuously receive reports that demonstrate that 98.0% of the energy values are collected to HES within 4 hours after the daily shift."
  },
  {
    "ID": "T-37",
    "Purpose": "Communication metadata should continuously be delivered",
    "Test steps": "Verify that communication metadata is logged every other hour in the Measurement Unit. Verify that communication metadata is sent to HES at least once per day"
